The Lagos State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has expressed shock and sadness over the death of its State Woman Leader, Hon Mrs Shola  Oladeinbo, but charged the family to be comforted by the fact that Mrs Oladeinbo left behind a good legacy. Expressing the party’s shock in a statement, the chairman of the party in the state, Mr. Adedeji Doherty said, “I am saddened by the news of the passage of the PDP Lagos State Woman Leader, Hon Mrs Shola  Oladeinbo.” He urged the family members to heart about the development, saying that “The death of a parent always conveys an unnerving feeling of finality and sense of loss that leaves sorrow in the heart of mortals. “Please be comforted by the fact that your Mother’s legacies and contributions to the growth of our Party the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP)and his immediate community will continue to endure, having nurtured and mentored the women around her to a greater height. “On behalf of myself, my family and the entire members of PDP Lagos State, I hereby extend our deepest condolences to the entire family over this great lost. “I pray that Almighty God will comfort the family and grant the deceased eternal rest and reward her good virtues while she lived.”